                  </persName>
            , a pawnbroker: I received this watch, on the 4th of October, 1796, in the name of Thomas Morris, of Enfield; I do not know that the prisoner is the man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17980418-80-person645">
                  JONATHAN
                   TROTT
               <interp inst="t17980418-80-person645" type="surname" value="TROTT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17980418-80-person645" type="given" value="JONATHAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17980418-80-person645" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - On the 16th of June, 1797, I received a warrant to apprehend the prisoner at the bar: I took him at Luton, in Bedfordshire, on the 6th of March.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. I went to the privy. and found this watch lying upon the seat, and I came into the house and enquired if any body owned such a thing, and nobody owned it.</p>
               <p>GUILTY (Aged 34.)</p>
               <p>Of <rs id="t17980418-80-verdict420" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17980418-80-verdict420" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17980418-80-verdict420" type="verdictSubcategory" value="lesserOffence"></interp>
               stealing, but not privily from his person
            </rs>.</p>
